--- body ---
## Context

PR #85 (merged 2026-05-03, commit aa7e40e) rewrote `skills/ticket-close/SKILL.md`
to delegate to `${ERG:-erg} close <id> <reason>`. The skill's
frontmatter now reads `argument-hint: <ticket-id> [reason]` — the
reason-argument capability that ticket 0077 originally proposed.

But the `erg` Go binary in `tickets/tools/go/main.go` does **not**
implement a `close` subcommand. The dispatch table at the bottom of
`main.go` covers `validate / ready / archive / graph / next-id` only.
Running `/ticket-close <id> done` on main today fails with
`Unknown command: close` and the ticket file is not mutated — the
`Status:` field stays `open`.

This silently breaks the PR #89 CLOSED-loop path in pick-ticket:

1. pick-ticket detects exit criteria are met for an open ticket
2. pick-ticket invokes `/ticket-close <id>` (no reason) — fails silently;
   ticket stays `open`
3. pick-ticket appends a `sweep-close: already-done` log line manually
4. Beat receives `CLOSED: <id>`, loops back, picks the next candidate
5. Next beat: same ticket is still `open`, gets picked again, same
   exit-criteria match, same flow — until `MAX_CLOSED_REPICKS=3` aborts

The pick-ticket cleanup that 0077 also proposed (drop the hand-written
`sweep-close:` line, call `/ticket-close <id> already-done` directly)
is also still owed.

## Goal

Make `/ticket-close <id> [reason]` actually close tickets on main, and
remove the layering wart in pick-ticket.

## Two scope options

**Option A — ship `erg close` in the Go binary** (long-term right;
aligns with ticket 0057 vision of routing all .erg mutations through
erg):
- Add `cmdClose(args []string) int` in `main.go`
- Locate the ticket file by id, set `Status: closed`, append the status
  log line `{ts} {actor} status closed — {reason}` (UTC minute), commit
  the change with the existing `git add tickets/ && git commit -m`
  pattern (or just leave the commit to the caller; current SKILL.md does
  it externally)
- Wire it into the dispatch table at line ~1132 of `main.go`
- Add Go tests covering: existing open ticket closes; idempotency on a
  closed ticket; missing id errors cleanly; reason default of `done`
  when omitted

**Option B — revert merged ticket-close to a Markdown procedure that
works today** (pragmatic, what 0077 originally proposed):
- Restore the pre-#85 SKILL.md flow but with the `[reason]` parsing
- Two-step: edit Status line + append log line; commit
- Defer the erg-binary delegation until git-erg ships `erg close`

Recommendation: **A**. The branch-as-claim and erg-mutation direction
is already chosen; one-shot fix here also satisfies the close-path
slice of ticket 0057.

## Pick-ticket cleanup (regardless of option)

Update `skills/pick-ticket/SKILL.md` step 4:

- Drop the manual `sweep-close: already-done hash:<bodyhash>` log-line
  append.
- Call `/ticket-close <id> already-done` (single command, no second
  step).
- The status log line `{ts} claude status closed — already-done` then
  serves the same audit purpose as the current `sweep-close:` line.
- Update any tests / audit greps to match `status closed — already-done`
  instead of `sweep-close: already-done`. Or — if the `sweep-close:`
  audit pattern is more grep-friendly — have the ticket-close skill
  (Option A: in erg, Option B: in Markdown) emit BOTH a `status` line
  and a `sweep-close:` line when called with `already-done`. Decide
  which convention to keep before implementing.

## Test

- Go test: `TestCmdClose` covers the four cases above (Option A only).
- Bash test: `tests/test_ticket_close_reason.sh`
  - Create a temp .erg ticket
  - Invoke `/ticket-close <id> done` (or the underlying `erg close`)
  - Assert the resulting `Status:` line and the appended status log
    line match expected patterns
- Existing pick-ticket tests should be reviewed; the CLOSED-loop test
  in test_beat.py (PR #89) currently mocks `/ticket-close` so it does
  not exercise the real bug. Consider an integration test that runs
  pick-ticket against a fixture and asserts the ticket's `Status:`
  field is `closed` after the loop.

## Exit criteria

- `/ticket-close <id> [reason]` mutates the ticket file: `Status: closed`
  + status log line with the reason. Verified by reading the file after
  the call.
- pick-ticket no longer hand-writes a `sweep-close:` line; the close
  path is one command.
- Existing audit tooling that greps for the close-with-reason pattern
  continues to match.
- `MAX_CLOSED_REPICKS=3` no longer fires from already-done loops on a
  test fixture.

